Of the thousands of U.S. troops getting discharged from the Army each year, many who are suffering from post traumatic stress disorder and brain injuries aren&amp;#039;t getting the vital care they need. The Army claims these soldiers have pre-existing mental illnesses or are guilty of misconduct. But advocates say this is a way for the Army to get rid of &quot;problem&quot; soldiers quickly, without giving them the treatment and benefits to which they&amp;#039;re entitled. This week, NOW travels to Fort Hood in Texas to meet traumatized soldiers fighting a new battle, this one against the army they served. Are soldiers being wrongfully discharged for honorable service? Support your local PBS Station by making a contribution or by purchasing their DVDs. Shunster online video available
